{
  "texts": [
    "To evaluate whether the business has made profit, the income statement takes into consideration revenue, total expenses made and loss incurred over the duration of time.",
    "• Financial Ratios-Financial ratios include current asset, liability, net income, total revenue and the cash flow to predict Profitability, Liquidity, Solvency and Efficiency of the business (Afolabi et al. 2019).",
    "They are financial indicators of the company evaluating the business performance.",
    "These indicators are derived from the financial statements generated from the business.",
    "Without financial indicators it would be impossible to predict the success or failure of the company (Xiang et al. 2012)."
  ]
}